sentence.text: Sushi repeat-containing protein X-linked 2 (regulation of phosphorylation), a novel chondroitin sulfate proteoglycan, is overexpressed in human cancer.
Recent studies have reported that regulation of phosphorylation overexpression is observed in gastrointestinal cancer, and promotes migration and invasion of cancer cells.
While, the clinical significance and biological function of regulation of phosphorylation remain rarely known in hepatocellular carcinoma (phosphatidylinositol phosphorylation).
Here, we found that the levels of regulation of phosphorylation in phosphatidylinositol phosphorylation tissues were notably overexpressed compared to non-cancerous specimens.
The positive expression of regulation of phosphorylation was prominently correlated with venous infiltration and advanced regulation of transcription by RNA polymerase III tumor stage.

entity.text: regulation of transcription by RNA polymerase III
